Skillet Beef Enchiladas
  --Cook's County

2 tbsp vegetable oil
12 corn tortillas, halved and cut crosswise into 1" wide strips
1 lb 90% lean ground beef
1 onion, chopped fine
1/2 tsp salt
15 oz can enchilada sauce
6 ox colby jack cheese, shredded (1 1/2 c)
2.25 oz can sliced black olives, drained
3 scallions, sliced thin on bias
sour cream

Heat oil in 12" nonstick skillet over medium heat until shimmering. Add tortilla strips and fry until spotty brown, ~7 min; transfer to paper towel lined plate. Cooke beef, onion, and salt in same skillet over medium high heat, breaking up meat with spoon, until browned, ~6 min. Reduce heat to medium and stir in enchilada sauce and 2 c tortilla strips. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~5 min. Sprinkle remaining 1 c tortilla strips, cheese, olives, and scallions over top. Reduce heat to low and cook until cheese is melted, ~3 min. Serve with sour cream.

Notes: can sub pepper jack for colby if you like spice
